as for dps, a full equiped wizard can outdamage a mage, hands down, but getting our spells/focus items is harder... when has being a wizard been an 'easy' class (unless you suck, eh Valt <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  we've always had to work harder, but are the best in the end... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andraelarcaneumrunner>Andrael Arcaneumrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Hand Of<BR>The Cabal (tm)!!!</span><br>  Posts: 1348<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/6/03 11:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At this point...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>but are the best in the end... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That is no longer so.  The old &quot;I had to deal with X but I get it all back in the end&quot; is pretty much invalidated.<br>
<br>
Are we gimps?  Hell no.  I kick ass cause I play my class well.  Are we the magical masters of damage now?  Nope.  Even before POP Mages and their pets came close, but we could shine brightly in the right situation and type of fight.  Now?  We rank behind Mages in general and Chanters with the new charm, but I doubt that particular Chanter issue will be around much longer.<br>
<br>
To be fair: A few wizards at the higher end with many AA/awesome gear/highest guilds can own.  They have no issues with how things stand for obvious reasons.  But having a few of those online out of 100,000 others online doesnt mean much for the class.  Or to put it another way.  The existance of a Froz doesnt mean that I, at a lower level and compared against mages of the same level/AA's as myself, am balanced.<br>
<br>
I am a very good wizard and we kick ass as a caster class, but we arent the best as of POP.  Lots will disagree with that, some screeching, some insulting, and some will arrogantly claim they must know the class better.  Thats OK.   A lot of it is pride on their part and an unwillingness to see the game has changed.   I personally still kick ass, control my agro, know eeeeeeeeexactly when to pour the coals to a mob and when to evac my group out without them saying a word..  I am a valuable damn wizzy and play a valuable damn role.   I am not overly jealous of mage dps, but nor do I try to ignore the new state of things.  I just continue to kick ass and thats what you should try to do also.  Spend less time concentrating on others DPS and more time on kicking ass, above all enjoy the game<br>
<br>
/wave<br>
<br>
Andrael<br>
<br>
