<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=289810" target="top">Nalianna</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tehutibloodstorm>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Blueberry Nuker</span><br>  Posts: 1299<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/7/03 5:58 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At this point...</span><hr size=1> Wizards aren't gimped magicians, magicians are gimped wizards.<br>
<br>
All their firepower is in one little mob, I go places solo where a magician would be completely screwed. Yes they have a handy dandy pile of goo running around spouting about how wonderful their &quot;master&quot; is.<br>
<br>
Yet consider their primary limitation:<br>
<br>
A) Any place they go they have to consider pathing problems. We look <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>forward</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to pathing problems, they give us an added edge.<br>
<br>
They're fairly self-contained, summoning what items they need. We're smarter, we pop into any city we want, talk to an inkeeper, pop a couple of beers, pinch the barmaids cheeks. You name it. Magician is roughing it, maybe feeling up his hot date (read fire pet).<br>
<br>
A wizard is completely self-sufficient in their capabalities. We can stun, we can root, we can nuke the hell out of any damn thing. One of our best abilities, is reverse healing. People underestimate shield spells, they prevent damage! They give us phantom hit points, you look at your hit point screen, you read 200, 800, 1000 hit points. You better read again, and tally in your skin spell. Keeping up a skin spell for hot pulls is a life saver, you can have 2 HP's pull of a skin spell and you've saved your life. <br>
<br>
Not to mention that snare, roots are godly. <br>
<br>
A magician better hope to hell his invisibility holds, due to the fact that unless he has time to set up for his endeavors he's almost certainly screwed.<br>
<br>
No one does it faster, or more efficiently.<br>
<br>
People say we don't have heals, no way to regen HP's. This is partly true, bandaging to half health, plus a skin spell puts you technically at a 75% rating for health. If you want quicker heals, quicker regen read, read the last part of this post.<br>
<br>
The thing to remember being a wizard is something more than what the class is. It involves thought, you go into a zone blasting the hell out of things, unless you're in newbieville, you're screwed.<br>
<br>
Your like the lightning bolt from the sky, choose your targets, decide what needs to die and more importantly <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>when</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Being a wizard requires forethought, careful consideration of when and how to apply yourself.<br>
<br>
Being a wizard is a great thing.<br>
<br>
<br>
For those wanting heals, and regen:<br>
<br>
You can't heal yourself, you wish every day you could summon bandages, you can't cure anything, you can't run fast, hell it just sucks to be you sometimes.<br>
<br>
But, what if you could heal yourself, what if you could cure that dot killing you at this moment, what if you could do what everyone says can not be done?<br>
<br>
Heals: 300 pt heal, self; Regen +20 hit points/tick for 2 minutes<br>
<br>
Cure disease, cure poison<br>
<br>
Unfortunately the game does not allow you to practice alchemy.... ever. <br>
<br>
However with some porting, and some creative uses of your platinum you can round yourself out very nicely.  Find out who your local alchemy masters are, most will do the combine for free if you bring the materials.<br>
<br>
<br>
Granted some are expensive, in remarks to the regen potions, and the heal potions. Yet consider, how much would that rez cost you.... or even if you can find a cleric....<br>
<br>
<br>
